name: Buckle Up (Kamigawa: Neon Dynasty Commander Precon Decklist)

main.name: Kotori, Pilot Prodigy
main.oracle_text:
Vehicles you control have crew 2.
At the beginning of combat on your turn, target artifact creature you control gains lifelink and vigilance until end of turn.
main.flavor_text: "Some people test limits. I prefer to demolish them."

card.oracle_text:
Menace

Crew 4

Whenever one or more Vehicles you control attack, create a 1/1 colorless Pilot creature token with "This creature crews Vehicles as though its power were 2 greater."
Crew 2 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 2 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

card.name: Mobilizer Mech
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever Mobilizer Mech becomes crewed, up to one other target Vehicle you control becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.
Crew 3 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 3 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

card.name: Imperial Recovery Unit
card.oracle_text:
Whenever Imperial Recovery Unit attacks, return target creature or Vehicle card with mana value 2 or less from your graveyard to your hand.
Crew 2 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 2 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

card.name: Kappa Cannoneer
Imposter Mech

You may have Imposter Mech enter as a copy of a creature an opponent controls, except it's a Vehicle artifact with crew 3 and it loses all other card types.
Crew 3
card.flavor_text: The best way to fight evil is with its own weapons.

card.name: Access Denied

card.flavor_text: The Saiba Futurists guard their secret experiments with ever-evolving networks of cutting-edge defensive technology.

card.name: Research Thief
card.oracle_text:
Flash
Flying
Whenever an artifact creature you control deals combat damage to a player, draw a card.
card.flavor_text: The Futurists eagerly supplement their research with their rivals' closely guarded secrets.

card.name: Cyberdrive Awakener
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Other artifact creatures you control have flying.
When Cyberdrive Awakener enters, until end of turn, each noncreature artifact you control becomes an artifact creature with base power and toughness 4/4.

card.name: Ironsoul Enforcer
card.oracle_text: Whenever Ironsoul Enforcer or a commander you control attacks alone, return target artifact card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: "You break it, you buy it. You steal it, I find it."

card.name: Universal Surveillance
card.oracle_text:
Improvise (Your artifacts can help cast this spell. Each artifact you tap after you're done activating mana abilities pays for {1}.)
Draw X cards.
card.flavor_text: Few outside the Saiba Futurists know the true extent of their data-extraction network.

card.name: Katsumasa, the Animator
card.oracle_text:
Flying
{2}{U}: Until end of turn, target noncreature artifact you control becomes an artifact creature and gains flying. If it's not a Vehicle, it has base power and toughness 1/1 until end of turn.
At the beginning of your upkeep, put a +1/+1 counter on each of up to three target noncreature artifacts.

card.name: Swift Reconfiguration
card.oracle_text:
Flash
Enchant creature or Vehicle
Enchanted permanent is a Vehicle artifact with crew 5 and it loses all other card types. (It's not a creature unless it's crewed.)
card.flavor_text: On the bright side, the bear now had cupholders.

card.name: Drumbellower
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Untap all creatures you control during each other player's untap step.
card.flavor_text: By the second night after the kami had drifted into town, the local general store was completely sold out of earplugs.

card.name: Organic Extinction
card.oracle_text:
Improvise (Your artifacts can help cast this spell. Each artifact you tap after you're done activating mana abilities pays for {1}.)
Destroy all nonartifact creatures.
card.flavor_text:
"Technology evolves faster than a blade can swing."
—Arima, lead inventor of the Futurists

card.name: Aerial Surveyor
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever Aerial Surveyor attacks, if defending player controls more lands than you, search your library for a basic Plains card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
Crew 2

card.name: Release to Memory
card.oracle_text: Exile target opponent's graveyard. For each creature card exiled this way, create a 1/1 colorless Spirit creature token.
card.flavor_text:
"Those who have passed are beyond war, beyond suffering. Mourn them, envy them, but above all, remember them."
—Light-Paws, Imperial advisor

card.name: Skycloud Expanse
card.flavor_text: Remote but always watching, the soaring city of Otawara moves over Kamigawa with a purpose that few understand.

card.name: Etherium Sculptor
card.oracle_text: Artifact spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.
card.flavor_text: The greatest masters of the craft abandon tools altogether, shaping metal with hand and mind alone.

card.name: Master of Etherium
card.oracle_text:
Master of Etherium's power and toughness are each equal to the number of artifacts you control.
Other artifact creatures you control get +1/+1.
card.flavor_text: "Only a mind unfettered with the concerns of the flesh can see the world as it truly is."

card.name: Armed and Armored
card.oracle_text: Vehicles you control become artifact creatures until end of turn. Choose a Dwarf you control. Attach any number of Equipment you control to it.
card.flavor_text: The dwarves of Axgard seldom have reason to leave their impregnable underground kingdom—but when they do, they go in force.

card.name: Aeronaut Admiral
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Vehicles you control have flying.
card.flavor_text: The Consulate recruits its best pilots from the League of Aeronauts. Many go on to command entire fleets.

card.name: Dispatch
card.oracle_text:
Tap target creature.
Metalcraft — If you control three or more artifacts, exile that creature.
card.flavor_text: Venser wondered if it could still be called a teleportation spell if the destination is oblivion.

card.name: Swords to Plowshares
card.oracle_text: Exile target creature. Its controller gains life equal to its power.
card.flavor_text: "The arc of my blade has carved a path of light for the peace that will follow."

card.name: Colossal Plow
card.oracle_text:
Whenever Colossal Plow attacks, add {W}{W}{W} and you gain 3 life. Until end of turn, you don't lose this mana as steps and phases end.
Crew 6 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 6 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

card.name: Foundry Inspector
card.oracle_text: Artifact spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.
card.flavor_text: Automaton inspectors ensure that the Consulate's stringent standards for mass production are upheld.

card.name: Hanna, Ship's Navigator
card.oracle_text: {1}{W}{U}, {T}: Return target artifact or enchantment card from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: "I never thought I'd spend my life fighting. I'm a maker, not a destroyer."

card.name: Spire of Industry
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}, Pay 1 life: Add one mana of any color. Activate only if you control an artifact.
card.flavor_text: A beacon of prosperity to some, a shadow of oppression to others.

card.name: Arcane Signet
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: It started as a mere drop of water. The Magic Mirror crystallized it into much more.

card.name: Solemn Simulacrum
card.oracle_text:
When Solemn Simulacrum enters, you may search your library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
When Solemn Simulacrum dies, you may draw a card.

card.name: Command Tower
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: When defeat is near and guidance is scarce, all eyes look in one direction.

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.

card.name: Exotic Orchard
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color that a land an opponent controls could produce.
card.flavor_text:
"It was a strange morning. When we awoke, we found our trees transformed. We didn't know whether to water them or polish them."
—Pulan, Bant orchardist

({T}: Add {W} or {U}.)
Prairie Stream enters tapped unless you control two or more basic lands.

{T}: Add {W} or {U}.

card.name: Azorius Signet

{T}: Add one mana of any color.
